The Thracian fighter would often engage with him, and the Retiarius many a time, and would come up to him with his Net in his hand, ſinging this;


Non te peto, piſcem peto,

Quid me fugis, Galle?

And again;


Volucres quas excipit amne quieto

Mincius.
